snippet.textDisplay:
I’m a new subscriber and am in love with watching Dr Mike! ❤️❤️❤️
I’m a medical coder and really love watching medical shows. When I was in school, some of our assignments were to watch House and other medical shows and while we watched we would have to code any diagnoses that were mentioned and the patient’s final diagnosis. It was a really fun way to gain necessary knowledge and skills for coding. Long story, but I was wondering if you have reviewed any episodes of a show called the “Monsters Inside of Me”. That was always a fun one to watch. It’s not a drama, but instead a patient’s true story of dealing with illness that gets misdiagnosed and then their journey to finding what is actually wrong with the patient. It’s very interesting and shows how easily this can happen and the importance of different specialties working hand in hand with abnormal cases. Would love to see you review any one of the episodes!
